metabolic imbalances such as electrolyte disturbances can disrupt normal neurological functions resulting in altered levels of consciousness.', 'Intracranial hypertension - increased pressure within the skull, regardless of its cause, can compromise cerebral blood flow and brain function leading to lethargy or coma.', "Hypoxic-ischemic encephalopathy (HIE) -
